Turns a crosstable object into a formatted gt table

Source: R/gt.R
as_gt.Rd

Turns a crosstable object into a formatted gt table

Generic method

# S3 method for crosstable
as_gt(
  data,
  show_test_name = TRUE,
  by_header = NULL,
  keep_id = FALSE,
  generic_labels = list(id = ".id", variable = "variable", value = "value", total =
    "Total", label = "label", test = "test", effect = "effect"),
  ...
)

as_gt(data, ...)

Arguments

data
show_test_name

in the test column, show the test name
by_header

a string to override the by header
keep_id

whether to keep the .id column
generic_labels

names of the crosstable default columns
...

Methods (by class)

  • crosstable: Turns a crosstable object into a formatted gt table.

See also

as_flextable.crosstable()

gt::gt()

Examples

xx = mtcars2 %>% select(1:9)
crosstable(xx) %>% as_gt
